snippet.textDisplay: The thing with IE not being able to die is that there are a lot of engineers and probably other professionals who do a lot of data reduction automation with Excel and VBA. Microsoft has another ancient programming language called VBscript they developed as a competitor to Javascript, which is almost identical to VBA, and only runs on IE. It's mostly dead, but it lives on because allows you to write GUIs for VBA scripts as web pages. It also allows other various desktop/workstation tasks to be automated without really learning a new language. Theoretically, it could be run from a command prompt, but then you lose the GUI aspect.
